phase 4: native polish + lite build + windows/mac CI

Native feel:
- custom title bar with drag region + traffic-light buttons
- themed React context menu (Tauri native menus look bad on GTK)
- streaming token batcher (RAF-batched, drops per-token reflow)
- typing-lag fix (ref-based content, no per-keystroke setTabs clone)
- spellcheck/autocorrect off on the editor
- WebKitGTK env vars + chat scroll containment

Lite build (default):
- llama-cpp-2 is now optional behind `local-llm` Cargo feature
- default deb drops 397 MB → 15 MB
- new `runtime_capabilities` IPC; AISettingsModal hides Local GGUF tab
  in lite builds. Users run local LLMs via Ollama (openai_compat).

Distribution:
- icon design (warm-amber F mark) + tauri icon generation
- bundle metadata (category, descriptions, debian section)
- new GitHub Actions release workflow: tri-platform matrix
  (Linux deb/AppImage, Windows msi/nsis, macOS dmg arm64+x86_64),
  workflow_dispatch + tag-triggered

Wikilinks:
- StateEffect-driven decoration rebuild on tree-load
  (fixes [shortRef] not being clickable until manual read/write toggle)

